@SylvLima It drives me nut when people w some influencer quote me higher than what I get from A-lister.
It is true that influencer/bloggers need to pay bills, but you rate should reflect the value you can add.
That is why some people are A-list influencers...and others stay C-list forever.
And C list influencers in Canada charge higher and refuse to do the work. This diva attitude needs to be killed.
I work with A list influencers who are down to earth and WORK CRAZY HARD to delivery VALUE.
Canadian influencer rates are a JOKE. I think I should reply, I will spend my money on ads. It is cheaper and more effective.
Influencers need to be more realistic. Base your rate on the VALUE you can offer.
